📜 Code of Conduct

🌟 Our Commitment

We are committed to fostering an open, inclusive, and respectful environment for everyone.
All contributors, users, and participants are expected to uphold this standard.

---

🤝 Expected Behavior

- Be respectful and considerate in all interactions
- Communicate constructively and professionally
- Welcome diverse perspectives and ideas
- Provide helpful feedback and support
- Focus on collaboration and learning

---

❌ Unacceptable Behavior

The following behaviors are not tolerated:

- Harassment, discrimination, or offensive comments
- Personal attacks or abusive language
- Trolling or disruptive behavior
- Sharing private or sensitive information without permission
- Any conduct that creates an unsafe environment

---

⚙️ Responsibilities

Project maintainers are responsible for:

- Enforcing this Code of Conduct
- Reviewing and addressing reported issues
- Taking appropriate action when violations occur

---

🚨 Reporting Issues

If you experience or witness unacceptable behavior:

- Open an issue in the repository
- Or contact the maintainers directly

All reports will be handled respectfully and confidentially.

---

⚖️ Enforcement

Violations may result in:

- Warning or temporary restriction
- Removal from the project
- Permanent ban from contributing

---

📌 Scope

This Code of Conduct applies to:

- Project discussions
- Issues and pull requests
- All community interactions related to this repository

---

🏁 Final Note

We aim to build not just a powerful AI system, but also a positive and collaborative community around it.

Thank you for being respectful and contributing responsibly 🙌
